headlines.description: — Saddiq Bey scored 31 points and the Detroit Pistons rallied to beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 135-118 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bey, Bogdanovic lead shorthanded Pistons past Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma broke a tie with a 3-pointer with 5.7 seconds left and the Washington Wizards beat the Chicago Bulls 100-97 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuzma hits late 3-pointer to lift Wizards past Bulls, 100-97

headlines.description: — Jrue Holiday scored 27 points, Brook Lopez had 20 points and 12 rebounds and the Milwaukee Bucks held off the Atlanta Hawks 114-105 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Holiday, Lopez help Bucks hold off Hawks, 114-105

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — The numbers that Celtics stars Jaylen Brown and Jayson Tatum have been putting up this season point to a duo playing even better than last season when Boston reached the NBA Finals.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown scores season-high 41 points, Celtics beat Pelicans

events.name: Indiana Pacers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brunson scored 34 points to help the New York Knicks beat the Indiana Pacers 119-113 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson, Barrett help Knicks hold off Pacers, 119-113

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 38 points, Jaren Jackson added 21 points and 12 rebounds, and the Memphis Grizzlies hung on to beat the San Antonio Spurs 135-129 Wednesday night for their season-high eighth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant scores 38 in return as streaking Grizzlies top Spurs

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 21 points, 18 rebounds and nine assists before sitting out the fourth quarter and the Denver Nuggets won their 12th straight home game, routing the weary and short-handed Phoenix Suns 126-97 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Nuggets rout Suns 126-97 for 12th straight home win

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 25 points, 14 rebounds and nine assists as the Sacramento Kings beat the skidding Houston Rockets 135-115 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis nearly has triple-double, Kings top skidding Rockets
